Allow paint to dry completely and then add your “dirt.”
Make dirt out of poly-fil and the brown jersey cotton material. Cut material to fit the width of your box, fold in half and then stitch along the edge, leaving a small opening on one side. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7a\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7a\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Fill jersey with poly-fil and then close hole by hand stitching. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d8\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d8\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Place in the box (once the paint is dry) and continue adding/creating “dirt” until you’ve filled the box. You should have small “rows” in between “dirt pillows.”{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Cut out a large purple circle and then cut 4 even triangles into the circle. Sew triangle sections together until you have a pouch. Add poly-fil, cinch the top and tie to close off. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Make long beat using long leaves made from green felt, covered with a long, pointed purple stalk. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Insert green pipe cleaner into long leaves so they stand up straight and sew leaves and beat together. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

text:
 Paint box and add “dirt.”  Cover the entire box with brown paint. Allow paint to dry completely and then add your “dirt.”
Make dirt out of poly-fil and the brown jersey cotton material. Cut material to fit the width of your box, fold in half and then stitch along the edge, leaving a small opening on one side. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7a\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7a\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Fill jersey with poly-fil and then close hole by hand stitching. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d8\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/d8\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Place in the box (once the paint is dry) and continue adding/creating “dirt” until you’ve filled the box. You should have small “rows” in between “dirt pillows.”{"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6d\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Make carrots. Cut a large triangle from the orange felt and fold in half. Stitch along the bottom edge. Cut out a circle to “top” your carrot, followed by a few green leaves from green felt. Sew leaves to the orange circle. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7f\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7f\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Stuff carrot with poly-fil and connect orange circle to the top of the carrot. Sew to close. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Create beats using the purple and green felt. Cut out a large purple circle and then cut 4 even triangles into the circle. Sew triangle sections together until you have a pouch. Add poly-fil, cinch the top and tie to close off. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/88\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Make long beat using long leaves made from green felt, covered with a long, pointed purple stalk. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/6b\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Insert green pipe cleaner into long leaves so they stand up straight and sew leaves and beat together. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/e7\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Add some strawberries. Cut out a circle that resembles a strawberry (so not a perfect circle). Create a pouch that can be filled with poly-fil. Sew top closed. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/fa\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/fa\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Add leafy green top by cutting out a 4-leaf top. Attach a piece of Velcro to the bottom of the leaf and the top of the strawberry. Put them together to form one strawberry. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/14\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/14\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"} Plant your garden. Stuff vegetables down in between dirt pillow rows. Allow your child to plant and “un-plant” his or her garden. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/01\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-459px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/01\/Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-5Bullet1.jpg\/v4-759px-Make-a-Plantable-Felt-Garden-Box-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}
